TITLE: Creating an Address and Assigning it to an Order in Sylius PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to programmatically create a new address using Sylius factory, set its properties like name, company, location details, and finally assign it as a shipping address to an order. It shows the complete workflow from address creation to order assignment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sylius/sylius/blob/2.1/docs/the-book/customers/addresses/addresses.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
/** @var AddressInterface $address */
$address = $this->container->get('sylius.factory.address')->createNew();

$address->setFirstName('Harry');
$address->setLastName('Potter');
$address->setCompany('Ministry of Magic');
$address->setCountryCode('UK');
$address->setProvinceCode('UKJ');
$address->setCity('Little Whinging');
$address->setStreet('4 Privet Drive');
$address->setPostcode('000001');

// and finally having the address you can assign it to any Order
