TITLE: Payment State Machine Transitions in YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration defines the possible transitions between different payment states in Sylius. It shows how payments can move through states such as cart, new, processing, authorized, completed, failed, cancelled, and refunded.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sylius/sylius/blob/2.1/docs/the-book/carts-and-orders/payments.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
transitions:
    create:
        from: [cart]
        to: new
    process:
        from: [new]
        to: processing
    authorize:
        from: [new, processing]
        to: authorized
    complete:
        from: [new, processing, authorized]
        to: completed
    fail:
        from: [new, processing]
        to: failed
    cancel:
        from: [new, processing, authorized]
        to: cancelled
    refund:
        from: [completed]
        to: refunded
```

