TITLE: Implementing Custom Catalog Promotion Action Validator in PHP for Sylius
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the implementation of a custom catalog promotion action validator in Sylius. It includes validation logic for the action's configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sylius/sylius/blob/2.1/docs/the-cookbook-2.0/how-to-add-a-custom-catalog-promotion-action.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Promotion\Action;

use Sylius\Bundle\PromotionBundle\Validator\CatalogPromotionAction\ActionValidatorInterface;
use Sylius\Bundle\PromotionBundle\Validator\Constraints\CatalogPromotionAction;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Context\ExecutionContextInterface;

final class CustomActionValidator implements ActionValidatorInterface
{
    public function validate(array $configuration, CatalogPromotionAction $constraint, ExecutionContextInterface $context): void
    {
        if (!isset($configuration['amount']) || !is_int($configuration['amount'])) {
            $context
                ->buildViolation('sylius.catalog_promotion_action.fixed_discount.not_valid')
                ->atPath('configuration.amount')
                ->addViolation()
            ;
        }

        if (isset($configuration['amount']) && $configuration['amount'] < 0) {
            $context
                ->buildViolation('sylius.catalog_promotion_action.fixed_discount.min')
                ->atPath('configuration.amount')
                ->addViolation()
            ;
        }
    }
}
```

