TITLE: Nested Hook in Twig Template
DESCRIPTION: This Twig code snippet shows how to fire a hook named `hook_name` inside another hookable.  Even though the hook's name is just `hook_name` within the template, it is configured as `parent_hook_name.hook_name` in the YAML configuration. The `{% raw %}{% endraw %}` tags prevent Twig from interpreting the `{% hook %}` tag, so the browser displays it as source code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sylius/sylius/blob/2.1/docs/the-customization-guide/customizing-templates.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
"<!-- Template content -->\n<div id=\"container\">\n    {% raw %}\n{% hook 'hook_name' %}\n{% endraw %} <!-- Its still the same name, but it is configured as parent_hook_name.hook_name.-->\n</div>\n<!-- Additional content -->"
```

